Photo, Artful Snatcher -- Los Angeles city trash collector Al Johnson figures 
he swings 11 tons of refuse a day aboard the garbage truck he mans. And, from 
his precarious perch on the back of the truck, he sometimes takes a shortcut by 
snatching a bag from the curb without hopping down, above. Johnson says the 
best part of his job is "getting off early." MEL MELCON / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
