<HEADLINE>
<P>
PILOT'S LICENSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a private pilot, with an instrument rating, I take flying seriously. I was 
outraged upon reading about the new regulations (The Nation, Sept. 1) making it 
easier to obtain a pilot's license! If anything, I have always felt that the 
regulations should be more stringent. There are enough incompetent pilots in 
their air right now. 
</P>
<P>
Flying is serious business; it is not a game. Planes are not toys on a string. 
Every pilot has a responsibility for his/her own safety as well as the safety 
of everyone else in the air and on the ground. 
</P>
<P>
I hope that the National Transportation Safety Board and other private pilots 
will put enough pressure on the FAA to reverse that decision and not let 
inexperienced thrill-seekers endanger our skies. 
</P>
<P>
PATRICIA M. OLSON 
</P>
<P>
West Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
