<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chiron Corp.: The Emeryville, Calif.-based biotechnology company reported a 
first-quarter net loss of $3.9 million, compared to a net loss of $2.4 million 
a year ago. Revenue totaled $7.6 million, up 7%. The results reflected a 
decrease in revenue from collaborative research agreements, an 27% rise in 
research and development expenses and a $581,000 charge to research and 
development due to the firm's decision to postpone construction of 
manufacturing facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
