<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Next year's Oscars won't come around until March 26, but the Academy of Motion 
Picture Arts and Sciences has already picked the producer. Producer-director 
Gilbert Cates, who has served two terms as president of the Directors Guild of 
America, will do the honors for the 62nd annual event at the Dorothy Chandler 
Pavilion of the Music Center. Cates also is in his sixth year on the academy's 
Board of Governors, representing the Directors Branch. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Cates 
</P>
