<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
REMOTE AIRCRAFT ORDINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has directed the city attorney to draft an ordinance that 
would ban the use of remote-control operated model helicopters and airplanes in 
city parks. 
</P>
<P>
The Recreation and Parks Commission at its Aug. 17 meeting said the operation 
of remote-control model aircraft is not compatible with heavy park use. 
</P>
<P>
Barbara Franklin-Moran, director of cultural and recreation services, said the 
city has received numerous complaints about the noisy and potentially dangerous 
model aircraft. She said the city will try to find another place for hobbyists 
to fly their aircraft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
