<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARVARD AT BEVERLY HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In its opener, Beverly Hills showed little defense against Lompoc and none 
against tailback Napoleon Kaufman, who led the Braves to a 45-24 rout of the 
Normans. Kaufman scored four touchdowns, including one on a 95-yard kickoff 
return and another on a 73-yard interception. He rushed for more than 140 yards 
as well. 
</P>
<P>
Harvard lost in its debut, to Blair, 10-8, but the Saracens received a standout 
performance from junior defensive back-wide receiver Iheanyi Uwaezuoke , who 
was born in Nigeria. Uwaezuoke, who presents difficulties not only to opponents 
but also to game announcers, was particularly effective on defense, making 10 
solo tackles, forcing a fumble and knocking down a pass. 
</P>
<P>
The Normans will play host to the Saracens at 3 p.m. Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
