<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: CITY OF INDUSTRY; 
</P>
<P>
GOLF INJURY CLAIM FILED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Diamond Bar Councilman Gary Werner is asking the City of Industry to pay him 
for damages he suffered when a golf ball ricocheted off a metal railing and hit 
him in the eye. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred July 6 when Werner was practicing hitting golf balls at 
the Industry Hills Golf Course Driving Range. He was rushed by paramedics to 
Queen of the Valley Hospital in West Covina, where he underwent surgery and 
received 21 stitches. 
</P>
<P>
Although most of the railing is covered with mesh to absorb the impact of stray 
golf balls, Werner said, "at the very end of the range, where I was, there was 
no mesh screen. It was negligence on the city's part." 
</P>
<P>
Werner's attorney, Marc Lebovitz, has filed a claim with the City of Industry 
asking that Werner be compensated for hospital expenses, potential plastic 
surgery and lost wages. Lebovitz said he hadn't calculated the total monetary 
amount but said in the claim it may exceed $100,000. 
</P>
<P>
Industry City Atty. Graham Ritchie was unavailable for comment Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
