<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
S. AFRICA POLICY REVISED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city's South Africa purchasing policy, adopted in May, has been revised 
after city staff members experienced problems implementing it. 
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the Board of Directors adopted revisions suggested by Directors 
Chris Holden and William Paparian. Among the revisions: 
</P>
<P>
Cash purchases under $500 are exempted. Originally, the policy involved all 
city money. 
</P>
<P>
City staff members are allowed to buy products from companies doing business in 
South Africa if all suppliers of the product conduct business there. 
</P>
<P>
Purchases without which the delivery of city services would be seriously 
impeded are allowed. 
</P>
<P>
Even with the revisions, Director Paparian said the city has one of the 
strictest South Africa policies in California. 
</P>
</TEXT>
