<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHO'S HOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
* Palos Verdes quarterback Blake Anderson scored touchdowns the first two times 
he touched the ball on a 95-yard kickoff return and a 92-yard punt return to 
spark the Sea Kings to a 47-7 win over North Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
* Serra running backs Dennis Gerard and Jerald Henry combined for 245 yards 
rushing and six touchdowns (three each) to lead the Cavaliers over Pasadena, 
40-0, in the successful debut of new Coach Leo Hand. 
</P>
<P>
* Chadwick wide receiver John Sheldon caught six passes for 76 yards and two 
touchdowns as the Dolphins opened the season with a 24-20 eight-man win over 
Campbell Hall. 
</P>
<P>
* Running back Mike Clairmont rushed for 211 yards and one touchdown to help 
Mira Costa match its win total of 1988 with a 14-0 shutout over El Segundo. 
</P>
<P>
Who's Not 
</P>
<P>
* Narbonne opens the football season Friday against Grant with a 21-game losing 
streak, currently the longest skid in the state. The Gauchos, coming off two 
straight 0-9 seasons, have not won since beating Franklin, 13-12, in the sixth 
game of 1986. 
</P>
<P>
* Coast Christian's string of 24 consecutive victories came to a thunderous 
halt Saturday with a 50-0 loss to Victor Valley Christian, ending the longest 
winning streak in California eight-man football history. 
</P>
<P>
* North Torrance, traditionally a slow starter, lost its opener to Palos 
Verdes, 47-7, to fall to 2-7 in non-league games in the last three years. 
</P>
<P>
* Bishop Montgomery managed only three net yards and no first downs in the 
second half of its 27-0 loss to Leuzinger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
