<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SOCCER POWER EDGES CLU, 1-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Romey headed in Scott Rommel's corner kick with 1:14 to play Wednesday as 
UC San Diego, the NCAA Division III defending champion, defeated Cal Lutheran, 
1-0, in a nonconference soccer match at Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran goalkeeper Dave Salzwedel posted 19 saves. 
</P>
<P>
In another nonconference match: 
</P>
<P>
CS San Bernardino 6, Occidental 0 -- Lewis Tierney had five saves for 
Occidental (0-3). 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego d. The Master's, 15-3, 15-10, 10-15, 15-6 -- Teresa Stanley had 13 
kills at Master's. 
</P>
<P>
Pierce d. Long Beach, 15-6, 10-15, 15-5, 15-5 -- Anna Suarez had 15 kills to 
lead Pierce (1-0). 
</P>
