<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: GRANT FACES OPENER MINUS TWO STARTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Grant High likely will open its football season against Narbonne on Friday 
without two projected starters -- tailback Shawn Booker and quarterback Andy 
Wells, both of whom are injured. 
</P>
<P>
Wells broke his ankle and is out indefinitely, and converted wide receiver 
Marlowe Lewis will play in his place, according to Grant Coach Bill Foster. 
</P>
<P>
Booker has an injured ankle and is questionable for Friday's game. Booker, who 
gained 654 yards in 120 carries for a 5.4 average as a junior, injured the 
ankle last week in practice and has not practiced since. Converted fullback 
Tony Johnson will take his place if necessary. 
</P>
<P>
Annette Burrows of Camarillo and Cynthia Pardee of Moorpark defeated Terri 
Wells and Allison Evans of Louisville, Ky., 7-5, 2-6, 6-3, to win the Plymouth 
Women's Doubles Challenge Division I title last week in Port Washington, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Burrows and Pardee advanced to the national event by winning a Southern 
California tournament and a regional tournament in San Francisco. Both were 
awarded a 1990 Plymouth Sundance automobile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
