<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAYOR WANTS COUNTY TO POLICE COMPTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The mayor of Compton is seeking voter approval to hire Los Angeles County to 
provide law enforcement and fire protection services because he said the city 
can no longer afford its own departments. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor Walter Tucker said the city is caught in a budget crunch and must cut 
corners. By contracting with the county, the city could reduce law enforcement 
and fire expenditures, which exceed $19 million annually, by about 50%, Tucker 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Already Tucker's proposal has drawn sharp criticism and the threat of a recall 
from residents and city officials who claim that fire and police protection 
will suffer if the county takes over. 
</P>
<P>
Tucker said he will seek to place the question before the voters during the 
general election next June. He must gather about 10,000 signatures -- 25% of 
the registered voters in the city -- to put the issue on the ballot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
