<TEXT>
<P>
The Athletics Congress announced that Racquel Andrews, a long jumper at Prairie 
View A&amp;M University, has been suspended from competition for two years 
after testing positive for a banned substance. 
</P>
<P>
Andrews, who is from Houston, tested positive in June at the U.S. intermediate 
track and field championships at San Jacinto College in Pasadena, Tex. 
Officials did not identify the banned substance. 
</P>
