<TEXT>
<P>
Dion Thurman, a former Bradley University basketball player, has been charged 
with possession of cocaine after a police raid that resulted in the seizure of 
four grams of crack cocaine, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Thurman, 21, was arraigned Monday and bond was set at $5,000. He was also 
charged with possession of cocaine with intent to deliver, and resisting 
arrest. 
</P>
<P>
If convicted, Thurman faces up to three years in prison. 
</P>
