</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israeli Trade Minister Ariel Sharon on Wednesday defended his call for the 
assassination of Palestine Liberation Organization Chairman Yasser Arafat and 
drew a comparison with what he said was former President Ronald Reagan's 
attempt to kill Libyan leader Moammar Kadafi. 
</P>
<P>
