<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARITY SCORECARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The "Crystal Anniversary" party held at the Art Institute of Southern 
California in Laguna Beach on Sept. 9 raised about $15,000. 
</P>
<P>
Art lovers paid $125 each to dine on Chinese cuisine at the affair which 
celebrated the 15th anniversary of Designing Women, an arts support group 
founded by Muriel Reynolds. 
</P>
<P>
Among guests: Anne Colin; Jean Tandowsky; Beverly White; Joleen Parham; Nancy 
Snyder; Herta Anderson; and D. N. Evans, a Laguna Beach-based fashion creator 
who presented ethnic fashions during the evening. 
</P>
<P>
Susan Beechner was chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The "Western Barbecue" held in Eagle Country in Irvine on Sept. 7 raised about 
$25,000 for the Patty and George Hoag Cancer Center of Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Paul Coulter was chairman. 
</P>
<P>
"A Salute to Medical Research" party held at the South Coast Plaza Crystal 
Court in Costa Mesa on Sept. 9 raised about $20,000 for UCI Health Sciences. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Slemons and Ben Harris were co-chairmen. 
</P>
<P>
The cocktail party and art auction held at the Newport Beach home of Dr. and 
Mrs. Stephen Auerbach on Sept. 10 raised about $17,000 for the American 
Paralysis Assn. 
</P>
<P>
Jackie O'Hara and Jackie Allen were co-chairwomen. 
</P>
