<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: OCEANSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seven cars parked in a garage outside an Oceanside apartment complex caught 
fire Wednesday, a Fire Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The automobiles and garage were engulfed in flames at 2:19 a.m. when 
firefighters arrived at the two-alarm blaze in the 400 block of Brooks Street. 
</P>
<P>
Gasoline poured from the vehicles' burned fuel lines, causing an extreme fire 
danger, said Greg van Voorhees, an investigator for the Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
A resident of the complex heard an explosion, ran outside and saw two cars 
burning. She reported the blaze and attempted to control it with a fire 
extinguisher, but the blaze spread to the other five cars. Heat from the 
explosion damaged two additional cars nearby and a building 50 feet away, Van 
Voorhees said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was contained by 4 a.m. Its cause is under investigation. 
</P>
