SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CHULA VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police arrested a woman and a man Wednesday after witnesses heard gunshots and 
then reported seeing the woman beat an unidentified man with a handgun, force 
him into her car and drive away, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Rafaela Mendoza, 33, and Domingo Mendoza, 27, relationship unknown, were 
arrested at 3 p.m., about 90 minutes after several people heard gunshots in the 
200 block of Otay Valley Road, said Carol Bahler, a spokeswoman for the Chula 
Vista Police Department. Bahler said the two were booked on suspicion of 
assault with a deadly weapon. 
</P>
<P>
Chula Vista police found the suspects and the victim, who suffered gunshot 
wounds to the stomach, in the 1000 block of Raedel Street in Southeast San 
Diego. The victim was taken by ambulance to UC San Diego Medical Center, where 
he was undergoing surgery late Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
A 1983 Ford LTD with no license plates was impounded at the scene. Bahler said 
a .44-caliber revolver was found in the vehicle. 
</P>
