<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: OFFICER SHOOTS HIMSELF WHILE LOADING GUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An off-duty Los Angeles police officer shot himself in the leg while loading 
his revolver at home, authorities said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Christopher Kunz, 23, was at his home in the 12000 block of Eddleston Drive in 
Porter Ranch when his gun discharged about 5:50 p.m. Tuesday, Lt. William Hall 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The bullet passed through Kunz's right thigh. 
</P>
<P>
Kunz, who has been a Los Angeles police officer for a year and is assigned to 
patrol duty in the west San Fernando Valley, was in good condition at Holy 
Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills, Hall said. 
</P>
