<P>
ORANGE COUNTY HOME SALES DOWN 20% IN AUGUST FROM A YEAR AGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Home sales in Orange County dropped 20% in August from a year ago, according to 
TRW Real Estate Market Information. 
</P>
<P>
But last year was an unusually hot year for home sales, so this year's dip in 
sales was anticipated and represents a more normal market, experts said. 
</P>
<P>
TRW estimated that 4,431 homes were sold in the county in August, compared to 
5,613 last year. 
</P>
<P>
The average price of a home was $251,959, which includes both condominiums and 
houses. That rose 12% from a year ago, when the price was $195,023. 
</P>
<P>
TRW includes sales of both new and used homes in its calculations. 
</P>
<P>
There was some good news for the real estate industry in August's figures: The 
numbers represented a 28% increase in sales from July, probably because lower 
mortgage rates lured more buyers into the market. 
</P>
<P>
Only 3,461 homes were sold in Orange County in July, TRW said. The average 
price was actually a little bit higher in July, at $252,987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
