<P>
Christer Pettersson, sentenced to life in jail for the 1986 murder of Swedish 
Prime Minister Olof Palme, surprised his appeals court hearing today by 
confessing to 600 robberies. 
</P>
<P>
"I robbed 600 people between 1970 and 1977, two each week. . . . Most of them 
were amphetamine dealers," he told the Stockholm appeals court. 
</P>
