<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
QANTEL ARRANGES DEBT RESTRUCTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAYWARD, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qantel Corp. said today that it signed an agreement with a group of 10 banks to 
restructure the company's long-term debt. 
</P>
<P>
First National Bank of Boston is heading the banking group. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the agreement calls for the restructuring of $50 million of 
debt at a 7% interest rate over 10 years and includes a two-year moratorium on 
the principal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
