<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
SAN DIEGO WINS '92 ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 1992 All-Star Game will be played at San Diego's Jack Murphy Stadium on 
Tuesday, July 14, National League President Bill White said today following a 
meeting of baseball's executive council in Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
The Padres announced the selection in a statement this morning. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego, which last played host to the All-Star Game in 1978, beat Houston, 
Montreal and Philadelphia as potential sites for the game. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego business and community leaders made a presentation last June in 
Kansas City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
